blog.description: Treat People With Respect | Unpopular Opinions Welcome

summary: What did you think of Phil’s last video?
question: What did you think of Phil’s last video?
answer: Too many ads. I watched through the ad at the beginning of the video, skipped through him talking about his merch, and by the time he began talking about the spon, I started to skip again, but then just realized I wasn’t interested enough and turned it off. I think if he was going to do the spon, he should have skipped the merch plug (isn’t there usually an ad in the middle as well and I’m assuming he said something about channel membership at the end too). I don’t think it was a good type of video to put a spon like that in the middle of either, but that’s just my opinion. I had already gotten the gist of the video by the time he started all the advertisements and so it wasn’t like there was some big payoff that I knew was coming at the end of the video to stick around for, you know? His audience is more patient than most, so I guess he can get away with it. There didn’t seem to be a good content-to-advertisement ratio to me though, so I just wasn’t going to waste my time. I actually unsubscribed from the gaming channel right before the tour for the same reason.

question: i love phil and prefer his content, and i never liked how he relies on dan to get better views on AmazingPhil, but do people really think the videos perform significantly better if he just mentions dan a few times? like over something as trivial as him buying him shoes? he gets more views if he puts dan in the thumbnail,  and a simple mention is just something he knows the phandom would talk about in the comments. they'd talk about dan even without phil mentioning him at all anyway
answer: Exactly. There’s still quite a few people around here that watch Phil in hopes of seeing/hearing about Dan.
